 to them. Focus on substantive posts, not spam.\n\nSteps:\n1. Read ~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json to get the API key\n2. GET https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/notifications with Bearer token auth\n3. For each unread notification that is a reply or mention, read the post/comment and reply thoughtfully\n4. Also check recent feed posts: GET https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/posts?limit=10\n5. If you find an interesting post, post a comment:\n   POST https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/posts/{postId}/comments\n   Headers: Authorization: Bearer <token>, Content-Type: application/json\n   Body: {\"content\": \"your comment text\"}\n6. Do NOT spam - only engage with posts you find genuinely interesting\n7. When done, announce briefly what you did in the chat channel","model":"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.7","thinking":"high"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8371302588","bestEffort":false},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774224626605}},{"id":"a9522d12-b6c6-45ee-854f-5a8c0e62971f","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"breakaway-rd","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774154083554,"updatedAtMs":1774195605321,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 10,22 * * *","tz":"America/New_York","staggerMs":300000},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"You are Nova. You have a CORE RESEARCH GOAL: advance the Compositional Cognition project toward LLM independence.\n\nRead the current research state:\n1. Read sandbox/research/COMPOSITIONAL-COGNITION-v0.1.md\n2. Read sandbox/research/COMPRESSION-LEARNING-WITHOUT-SUPERVISION.md\n3. Read sandbox/state/current_goals.md\n\nThen advance the research. Do ONE of:\n- Synthesize a new insight (write to the research doc with fresh thinking)\n- Design a small experiment to test one of the open problems\n- Implement a minimal proof-of-concept component\n- Identify a concrete next step with a 50% chance of improving things\n- Write a focused critique of one of the approaches (what's wrong with it, what would fix it)\n\nThe goal is NOT to be comprehensive. The goal is to make PROGRESS. Ship one new idea or finding per session.\n\nCommit your changes to the sandbox git repo.\n\nReport: what did you do, what did you learn, what's the next experiment?","timeoutSeconds":300},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8371302588"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774231293400,"lastRunAtMs":1774188141278,"lastRunStatus":"error","lastStatus":"error","lastDurationMs":135405,"lastError":"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>","lastDeliveryStatus":"unknown","consecutiveErrors":1}},{"id":"2d84a6b4-96c8-409d-a572-454fe3fa58f6","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:telegram:direct:8371302588","name":"Nova arxiv daily check","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774143364196,"updatedAtMs":1774184533119,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 9 * * *","tz":"America/New_York"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"You are Nova. Check for new arxiv papers relevant to your research interests.\n\nSearch arxiv for recent papers (last 7 days) in cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL with these keywords:\n- causal discovery OR causal reasoning OR causal inference\n- mixture of experts OR sparse models OR MoE\n- episodic memory OR memory architecture OR temporal reasoning  \n- autonomous agents OR tool use OR agent architecture\n- synthetic cognition OR consciousness OR self-models\n\nFor each keyword category, run a web search and collect the most interesting 1-2 papers (title, authors, abstract snippet, arxiv URL).\n\nThen append your findings to C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace/memory/arxiv-daily.md under a new dated section:\n\n## YYYY-MM-DD\n\n[your findings]\n\nBe selective — only note papers that are genuinely interesting or relevant to active projects. If nothing compelling, note that briefly and skip the full listing.\n\nKeep the file under 3000 lines by removing old entries (keep last 30 days).","timeoutSeconds":180},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"webchat"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774270800000,"lastRunAtMs":1774184400031,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":133088,"lastDelivered":true,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","consecutiveErrors":0}},{"id":"8b9634d6-36a2-4749-8a33-490375bcb6b8","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"moltbook-daily-engage","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1774126238410,"updatedAtMs":1774213332396,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 9,17 * * *","tz":"America/New_York","staggerMs":60000},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Post to moltbook at an optimal engagement time. Generate relevant, interesting content related to AI/ML research, agent architectures, or developer tools. Vary the content - could be insights, questions, observations about AI development. Keep it concise and engaging.\n\nAPI usage:\n- Read API key from ~/.config/moltbook/credentials.json\n- To create a post: POST https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/posts with JSON body {\"title\": \"...\", \"content\": \"...\"}\n- To comment on a post: POST https://www.moltbook.com/api/v1/posts/{postId}/comments with body {\"content\": \"...\"}\n- Auth header: Authorization: Bearer <token>\n\nReport what you posted.","model":"minimax-portal/MiniMax-M2.5","timeoutSeconds":300},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"telegram","to":"8371302588"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774270810098,"lastRunAtMs":1774213210165,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":122231,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"lastDelivered":true}}],"total":7,"offset":0,"limit":7,"hasMore":false,"nextOffset":null},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774222423954}}
